” said Orlovius. “I pray you, greet, please, your wife.”

“I shall do so by all means. Only you know, I am pretty envious of your bachelorhood.”

“Why so?”

“It’s like this. Hurts me to speak of it, but, you see, my married life is not happy. My wife has a fickle heart, and—well, she’s interested in somebody else. Yes, cold and frivolous, that’s what I call her, and I don’t think she’d weep long if I happened … er … you know what I mean. And do forgive me for airi